# Style

Prettier (`prettier.config.js`: `semi: false`, `singleQuote: true`, `trailingComma: 'all'`) and ESLint (`eslint.config.js`, `@tanstack/eslint-config`) are the source of truth. Don't fight them; align new code so `yarn lint` and `yarn check` pass.

## Files & folders

- TypeScript files: **kebab-case** (`use-table-params.ts`, `auth-card.tsx`).
- Route files follow TanStack Router file-based conventions: `index.tsx`, `__root.tsx`, `posts.$postId.tsx`, `_layout.tsx`. Don't rename these to camelCase.
- Generated files (`src/routeTree.gen.ts`) are off-limits — the router plugin owns them.
- One concept per file; the filename reflects the primary export.

## Functions

- Do one thing — if the name contains "and", split it.
- Keep functions short; extract private helpers (prefixed `_`) when a function grows past ~45 lines (excluding blanks/comments).
- Pure where possible; side effects pushed to edges (route loaders, server functions, mutation handlers).

## Comments

- Only explain non-obvious **why**, trade-offs, or constraints.
- NEVER narrate **what** the code does (e.g., `// fetch data`, `// loop through items` — forbidden).
- TODO comments have an owner: `// TODO(@handle): reason`.
- JSDoc only for shared hooks/components reused across routes (with `@example` where helpful).

## Imports

- `verbatimModuleSyntax: true` is enabled in `tsconfig.json` → all type-only imports MUST use `import type { … }`. Mixed value + type from the same module is fine if both are needed.
- Drop dead imports before committing.
- No deep relative paths (`../../..`); use the project's path aliases.
  - **Prefer `#/*`** for new imports — it matches `components.json`, `package.json` `imports`, and `tsconfig.json` `paths`. shadcn-generated code writes `#/`.
  - `@/*` is also configured in `tsconfig.json` and acceptable. **Don't mix `#/` and `@/` in the same file** — match what the file already uses.
- The TanStack ESLint config disables `import/order`, `import/no-cycle`, and `sort-imports` (see `eslint.config.js`); Prettier handles spacing and quotes. Imports won't be auto-reordered, so keep them grouped manually: external packages → aliased project imports → relative imports → side-effect (`import './foo.css'`) imports.

## Constants

- All magic literals → a `constants.ts` (module-local first, package-shared next, `src/lib/constants.ts` last).
- Constant names: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (`MAX_RETRIES`, `REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS`).
- Reusable column projections / option sets used in more than one module → constants file with `as const`.

## Logging

- Structured logs only. No `console.log` in committed code. `console.warn` / `console.error` are allowed for genuinely unexpected failures and dev-only debugging.
- User-visible failures are surfaced via UI feedback (e.g., shadcn `Sonner` / `toast` once added) — not `console.error`.

## Tailwind class composition

- Always merge classes with `cn()` from `#/lib/utils`. Never string-concatenate Tailwind class names manually.
- Tailwind class order is auto-handled by `prettier` (the TanStack ESLint config does not override Prettier's class sorting). Don't hand-sort.
- Prefer **token utilities** (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-primary`) over arbitrary hex (`bg-[#173a40]`). Tokens live in `src/styles.css`.

## Commits (convention — not currently enforced by hooks)

- Conventional Commits: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`.
- Type + scope: lower-case (e.g., `feat(auth): add login route`).
- Subject required, no trailing period.
- Body / footer must be preceded by a blank line.

## Pre-commit (when added)

This repo has no pre-commit hook today. If one is introduced, the recommended runs on staged files are:

- `*.{ts,tsx}` → `yarn tsc --noEmit`
- `*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}` → `eslint --fix`
- `*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx,json,css,md,yml,yaml}` → `prettier --write`
